(164, 1, '2022-02-18 14:31:16', '2022-02-18 11:31:16', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Geometry topics, right triangles, special triangles, 30 60 90 triangle, 45 45 90 triangle, 15 75 90 triangle, 15 30 135 triangle, euclidean, pythagorus, magnificent triangles, special triangle questions according to sides and angles.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dik-ve-ozel-ucgenler-test1.jpg\" alt=\"dik ve özel üçgenler test1\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 1-) If ABC is a triangle, | AB | = | AC | = 9 cm, | AD | = 7 cm; | BD |. | DC | how many cm²?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/pisagor-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"pisagor soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 2-) In right triangle ABC, if [AD] perpendicular [BC], | AC | = 2 | AB |, | AD | = 4 cm; | BC | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/oklid-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"öklid soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 3-) If ABC right triangle, [BA] perpendicular [AC], [AN] perpendicular [BC], | BN | ² + | NC | ² = 112 cm², | AN | = 12 cm; | BC | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/45-45-90-ucgeni-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"45 45 90 üçgeni soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 4-) If [AB] perpendicular [BC], [CD] perpendicular [AD], m (BAD) = 45 °, | AB | + | BC | = 6 cm; | AD | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/15-30-135-ucgeni-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"15 30 135 üçgeni soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 5-) ABC is a triangle, if | AB | = 10 cm, m (BAC) = 15 °, m (ACB) = 135 °; | AC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dik-ucgen-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"dik üçgen soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 6-) If ABC is a triangle, | AB | = (root3) -1 cm, m (ACB) = 15 °, m (CBA) = 30 °; | AC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ozel-ucgen-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"özel üçgen soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 7-) ABCD is a quadrilateral, if [BA] perpendicular [AD], m (ADC) = 60 °, m (CBA) = 45 °, | AD | = 11 cm, | CD | = 6 cm; | BC | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/30-60-90-ucgeni-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"30 60 90 üçgeni soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 8-) ABC and KCN are each triangle, [AD] perpendicular [BN], | AD | = | KN |, | AK | = | KC | if; What is the measure of the KNB angle?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"special-right-triangles-test-1-answers\">Special right triangles test-1 answers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/dik-ve-ozel-ucgenler-test1-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"dik ve özel üçgenler test1 çözümleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In an ABC isosceles triangle (| AC | = | BC |), if a point of the base [BC] is D; | AD | ² = | AB | ²- | BD |. | DC | (x² = b-m.n).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>7² = 9²- | BD |. | DC | If written, | BD |. | DC | = 32 cm².</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/yukseklik-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"yükseklik çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 2- (1): From the Pythagorean relation in ABC triangle | BC | = k.rok5. If we say | BD | = x; | DC | = kkök5-x. In triangle ABC k² = x.kk root5, x = k / root5 from the Euclidean relation. If k / root5 is written instead of x, since k = 2 root5, then | BC | = 10 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/oklid-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"öklid soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 2- (2): The height of the hypotenuse in a right triangle is found by dividing the product of perpendicular sides by the hypotenuse. This is called the area relation. It is covered with the subject of the Euclidean theorem. For the proof of this formula and to prove other formulas, see the geometry proof section.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 3: In a right triangle, the height of the hypotenuse squared is equal to the product of the lengths it separates from the corners. This is called the Euclidean theorem.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/45-45-90-ucgeni-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"45 45 90 üçgeni soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: If the right triangle is also isosceles, then the hypotenuse is equal to the root2 times the perpendicular sides.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dik-ucgen-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"dik üçgen çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Let’s straighten the extension BC from corner A. Write instead of angles and call edge 5 opposite 30 °. Since the hypotenuse is equal to the root2 of the right sides in an isosceles right triangle, we write 5root2 for the length AC.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ozel-ucgenler-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"özel üçgenler soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: There are many solutions to these questions. We can solve them practically by creating a 30 60 90 triangle or a 45 45 90 triangle.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ozel-ucgenler-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"özel üçgenler çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In 30 60 90 triangle, the side opposite 30 ° is half the length of the hypotenuse, and in an isosceles right triangle the hypotenuse is equal to the root of the right sides.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/30-60-90-ucgeni-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"30 60 90 üçgeni soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In a right triangle, if one of the right sides is equal to half the length of the hypotenuse, this triangle is 30 60 90 and the opposite corner is 30 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":152,\"width\":191,\"height\":191,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/pdf-indir.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-152\" width=\"191\" height=\"191\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"has-text-align-center\" id=\"special-right-triangles-test-1-pdf\">Special right triangles test-1 PDF</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Course Geometry offers Geometry textbook in pdf format that can be downloaded free of charge. Students can view the special right triangles test-1 pdf, which is important for university entrance exam, which aims to improve students\' problem solving skills.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button aligncenter\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'Special Right Triangles Test-1', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'special-right-triangles-test-1', '', '', '2022-02-18 14:31:41', '2022-02-18 11:31:41', '', 0, 'http://localhost/geometri/?p=164', 0, 'post', '', 0);
