(143, 1, '2022-02-14 17:28:43', '2022-02-14 14:28:43', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the tests of angles in the line, we can act towards the solution with any of the angles formed by the interior opposite-contrast-opposite-external reverse angles, that is, two parallel lines and a line that intersects them. The most common of these is the interior reverse angles (z rule).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the angles between parallel lines, rules such as M-zigzag-pencil tip are defined. These rules emerge from the angles we mentioned at the beginning. We can obtain quick solutions by applying them to problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Straight angles solution questions, angles questions and solutions, right angles solved questions, angles in the line m rule, m rule, straight angles pencil rule, pencil point rule, straight angles test questions, straight angles solution questions 9th grade, test angles on the straight line …</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can review the images, from the end of the page 7.-8.-9 class in <strong>PDF</strong> format. You can download Angles on a straight line test-1 file to your computer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":128,\"width\":450,\"height\":454,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-01.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-128\" width=\"450\" height=\"454\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 1-) In the figure, A, B, C points are linear, m (EBA); All 1/3 of m (CBD) if m (CBD) = m (DBE) + 10 °; How many degrees is m (DBE)?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":129,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-02.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-129\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 2-) [FG parallel [BA, [FE] parallel [CD], if m (DCB) = 130 °, m (ABC) = 4x-10 °, m (EFG) = 3x; How many degrees is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":130,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-03.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-130\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":131,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-05.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-131\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 5-) [BE parallel if [CF, m (ABE) = 150 °, m (BAD) = 60 °, m (ADC) = 50 °; How many degrees is m (FCD) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":132,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-06.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-132\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 6-) [AF parallel [DE, [AC] perpendicular [BD], [AC] bisector, if m (BDE) = 145 °; How many degrees is m (DBA) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":133,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-07.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-133\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 7-) If FE parallel [CD, m (GAE) = 5y-5 °, m (DCB) = 3y + 5 °, m (GBC) = 60 °; How many degrees is m (FAB) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":134,\"width\":451,\"height\":455,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-08.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-134\" width=\"451\" height=\"455\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 8-) [BA parallel [FD, [KP parallel [BE, m (EBA) = 120º, if m (FKP) = 105º; How many degrees is m (CFK) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Parallel lines test-1 answers</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":135,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-09.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Test with direct angles solution for beginners</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":136,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-010.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-136\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Let the line segment that we will draw from point C are parallel to the lines given in the question. The desired angle measurement is obtained from the equation of parallel angles m (DCK) = 3x, internal opposite angles m (KCB) = 4x-10 °, from here 3x + 4x-10 ° = 130 °. Will be 20 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":137,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-011.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-137\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: The most practical solution to this question of the angles in the line test would be to see the parallel angles of the road sides or the opposite parallel angles.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":138,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-012.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-138\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: With the inside angles and the m rule, the desired angle x has a dimension of 100 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":139,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-013.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-139\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: If we intersect the extension [AB] and [CD] at one point, we find the angle x with the rule m since the third angle of the triangle is also known.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":140,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-014.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-140\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: The bisectors of the opposite state angles form a right angle. We can immediately write x on the angle between the parallel we have drawn [BK].</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":141,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-015.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-141\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: If we add the angles between parallel lines and equate them to 360 ° (pencil point rule), then y = 30 °, from the right angle x = 35 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":142,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/parallel-lines-examples-016.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-142\"/><figcaption>parallel lines test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Write m (ECF) = 120 ° from directional angles, 120 ° + 360 ° -x + 105 ° = 360 ° from pencil rule, measure of angle x is 225 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Parallel lines Test-1', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '125-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-02-14 17:28:43', '2022-02-14 14:28:43', '', 125, 'http://localhost/geometri/?p=143', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
