(153, 1, '2022-02-16 19:42:38', '2022-02-16 16:42:38', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Angles solutions in a line, angles in a line zigzag rule, zigzag rule, angles in a line questions and solutions, angles in a line test with answers, angles in a triangle question solution, shalwar triangle, triangles solved questions, right angles questions, triangles test …</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can review the images, from the end of the page 7.-8.-9 class in <strong>PDF</strong> format. You can download Angles on a straight line test-2 file to your computer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":151,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/9.sinif-dogruda-acilar-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-151\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 1-) [BA parallel [GH, if a + b + c + d = 590 °; How many degrees is x + y?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/dogruda-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"doğruda açılar soruları\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 2-) [AF parallel [DE, [AH] and [DG] bisector, if m (CBA) = 132 °, m (DCB) = 128 °; How many degrees is m (DGH) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/zikzak-kurali-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"doğruda açılar\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 3-) If [DF parallel [BC, [EA] perpendicular [AB], m (FDE) = 60 °, m (CBA) = 50 °; How many degrees is m (DEA) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/zikzak-kurali-ile-ilgili-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"zikzak kuralı ile ilgili sorular\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2c</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 4-) [GH parallel [FK, [DE] parallel [AF], [AB] bisector, m (CBA) = 80 °, m (BCD) = 35 °, m (EDC) = 70 °, m (FAG If) = 2x; How many degrees is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/dogruda-acilar-test-tyt.jpg\" alt=\"doğruda açılar test tyt\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 5-) [AL parallel [DK, [BP] and [CP] bisector, if m (LAB) = 38 °, m (KDC) = 138 °; How many degrees is m (BPC) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/dogruda-acilar-tyt.jpg\" alt=\"doğruda açılar tyt\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 6-) If a + b + c + d = 260 °, e + f = 20x; How many degrees is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/dogruda-acilar-sorulari-9.sinif_.jpg\" alt=\"doğruda açılar soruları 9.sınıf\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 7-) [If BL parallel [DE, m (LBP) = m (PBC), m (DCA) = m (ACB), m (PAC) = 15 °; How many degrees is m (CDE) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/paralel-dogruda-acilar-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"paralel doğruda açılar soruları\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 8-) If [BG parallel [DE, m (ABH) = m (HBG), m (EDF) = m (FDA), m (BAD) = 30 °; How many degrees is m (FCH) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"parallel-lines-test-2-answers\">Parallel lines test-2 answers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/dogruda-acilar-cozumlu-test.jpg\" alt=\"doğruda açılar çözümlü test\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: To find the sum of the angles between two parallel lines, we add the number of vertices between the parallel lines and multiply 1 by 180 °. (angle number-1) .180 ° From the sum of angles we have obtained, we find the desired value by subtracting the value given in the question.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/dogruda-aci-sorulari-ve-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"doğruda açı soruları ve çözümleri\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: (angle number-1). From the formula 180 ° (see the proofs section), a + b = 140 ° is found by the rule of M, 180 ° -x = a + b, and if a + b is substituted, x = 40 ° .<ins></ins></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/cozumlu-dogruda-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"çözümlü doğruda açı soruları\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Since the sum of the angles between two parallel lines on the same side is equal to the sum of the angles on the other side (zigzag rule), x + 130 ° = 120 ° + 90 °, x = 80 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/dogruda-aci-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"doğruda açı soru çözümü\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: With the sides (opposite) parallel angles, m (DEK) = 2x. The sum of the angles on the same side equals x = 25 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/dogruda-aci-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"doğruda açı çözümlü sorular\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: With the zigzag rule, it is 80 ° + x = a + b. If 80 ° + x is written in the triangle instead of a + b, 80 ° + 2x = 180 °, x = 50 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ic-ters-acilar-ornekler.jpg\" alt=\"iç ters açılar örnekler\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: From inside angles, m (BAD) = m (ABK) = a. From Zigzag rule a + b + c + d = e + f. 260 ° = 20x, x = 13 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/karsi-durumlu-acilar-sorulari-ve-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"karşı durumlu açılar soruları ve çözümleri\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In triangle ABC, m (BPC) = 15 ° + a (outer angle). [BL // [DE with inside angles 30 ° + 2a = 2a + m (KCD), m (KCD) = 30 °. From opposite angles m (CDE) = x = 150 ° is found.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/dogruda-acilar-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"doğruda açılar soru çözümü\"/><figcaption>Parallel lines test-2 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: [AK // [BG; m (DAK) = 2a-30 ° (inside angles). [AK // [DE; 2a-30 ° + 2b = 180 ° (opposite-state angles) .a + b = 105 °. [BG // [CL and [DE // [CP; m (BCL) = a, m (PCD) = b (corresponding angles) .a + x + b = 180 °, 105 ° + x = 180 °, m (FCH) = x = 75 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":152,\"width\":169,\"height\":169,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/pdf-indir.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-152\" width=\"169\" height=\"169\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"has-text-align-center\" id=\"geometry-parallel-lines-test-2-pdf\">Geometry parallel lines test-2 PDF</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Course Geometry offers Geometry textbook in pdf format that can be downloaded free of charge. Students can view the parallel lines test-2 pdf, which is important for university entrance exam, which aims to improve students\' problem solving skills.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button aligncenter\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'Parallel Lines Test-2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '150-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-02-16 19:42:38', '2022-02-16 16:42:38', '', 150, 'http://localhost/geometri/?p=153', 0,