(154, 1, '2022-02-16 20:26:47', '2022-02-16 17:26:47', '<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-acilar-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende açılar soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 1-) If ABC is a triangle, m (DBA) = m (DCB), m (BDC) = 143 °; How many degrees is m (CBA) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende açı soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 2-) If ABC is a triangle, m (BAD) = m (DAC), m (CBA) – m (ACB) = 32 °; How many degrees is m (ADB)?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/fuze-kurali-sorulari-7.sinif_.jpg\" alt=\"füze kuralı soruları 7.sınıf\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 3-) If ABC is a triangle, [AD] perpendicular [BD], m (DBA) = m (DAC), m (CBA) = 40 °; How many degrees is m (ACB) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/iki-ic-aciortay-arasindaki-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"iki iç açıortay arasındaki açı soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 4-) If ABC is a triangle, [BD] and [CD] bisector, m (BAC) = 2x, m (BDC) = 6x; How many degrees is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-aciortaylarin-olusturdugu-acilar-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende açıortayların oluşturduğu açılar soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 5-) [BE parallel [CF, [AP] and [DP] bisector, if m (ABE) = 141 °, m (FCD) = 151 °; How many degrees is m (DPA) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ic-aciortay-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"iç açıortay açı soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 6-) If ABC is a triangle, [AE] and [BD] bisector, m (BDC) = 115 °, m (AEB) = 76 °; How many degrees is m (ACB) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/iki-dis-aciortay-arasindaki-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"iki dış açıortay arasındaki açı soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 7-) If ABC is a triangle, [BD] and [CD] bisector, m (EAF) = 14x, m (CDB) = 11x; How many degrees is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/dis-aciortay-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"dış açıortay açı soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 8-) ABC is a triangle, [BD] and [CD] bisector, if m (EBF) = 44 °; How many degrees is m (ADC) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"angles-in-a-triangle-test-1-answers\">Angles in a triangle test-1 answers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-acilar-cozumlu-test.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende açılar çözümlü test\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 1: If the angle B is x, then the CBD angle is x-a. From the sum of the angles of the DBC triangle, x = 37 °</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 2: From the sum of the angles of the US triangle, x + n = 180 ° -m (ADB), in the ADC triangle from the outer angle y + n = m (ADB). Multiply the second expression by (-2) and add xy = 180 to the side by the first. ° -2m (ADB). If 32 ° is written instead of x, m (ADB) = 74 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-acilar-roket-kurali.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende açılar roket kuralı\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 3: The size of the angle formed when one side of the triangle is bent inward is x = a + b + c. The US concave quadrilateral contains x + a + 40 ° -a = 90 ° (shalwar, rocket, missile rule), x = 50 °. See geometry proofs section for proof of rule-Rocket rule-Missile rule and other proofs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 4: The size of the angle formed by the two inner bisectors in a triangle is 90 degrees more than half the size of the inside angle in the third corner, so 6x = 90 ° + x, x = 18 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ic-aciortay-ile-ilgili-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"iç açıortay ile ilgili çözümlü sorular\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 5: Let the extension [AB] and [DC] intersect at point K. With the rule of M, m (DKA) = 68 °. The dimension of the angle formed by the intersection of two bisector in the triangle AKD is x = 90 ° + (68 ° / 2) = 124 ° .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 6: Since [AE] and [BD] are bisectors in triangle ABC, m (AFB) = 90 ° + (x / 2). If the angles of the quadrant equal 360 °, then x = 34 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/iki-dis-aciortayin-kesisimi.jpg\" alt=\"iki dış açıortayın kesişimi\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 7: The measure of the angle formed by the two outer bisectors in a triangle is the complement of half the measure of the angle in the third corner. 11x = 90 ° – (14x / 2), x = 5 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 8: The angle between the two outer bisectors is x = 90 ° – (44 ° / 2) = 68 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":152,\"width\":187,\"height\":187,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/pdf-indir.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-152\" width=\"187\" height=\"187\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"has-text-align-center\" id=\"geometry-angles-in-a-triangle-test-1-pdf\">Geometry angles in a triangle test-1 PDF</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Course Geometry offers Geometry textbook in pdf format that can be downloaded free of charge. Students can view the angles in a triangle test-1 pdf, which is important for university entrance exam, which aims to improve students\