s=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/15-30-135-ucgeni-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"15 30 135 üçgeni soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 5-) ABC is a triangle, if | AB | = 10 cm, m (BAC) = 15 °, m (ACB) = 135 °; | AC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dik-ucgen-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"dik üçgen soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 6-) If ABC is a triangle, | AB | = (root3) -1 cm, m (ACB) = 15 °, m (CBA) = 30 °; | AC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ozel-ucgen-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"özel üçgen soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 7-) ABCD is a quadrilateral, if [BA] perpendicular [AD], m (ADC) = 60 °, m (CBA) = 45 °, | AD | = 11 cm, | CD | = 6 cm; | BC | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/30-60-90-ucgeni-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"30 60 90 üçgeni soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 8-) ABC and KCN are each triangle, [AD] perpendicular [BN], | AD | = | KN |, | AK | = | KC | if; What is the measure of the KNB angle?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"special-right-triangles-test-1-answers\">Special right triangles test-1 answers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/dik-ve-ozel-ucgenler-test1-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"dik ve özel üçgenler test1 çözümleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In an ABC isosceles triangle (| AC | = | BC |), if a point of the base [BC] is D; | AD | ² = | AB | ²- | BD |. | DC | (x² = b-m.n).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>7² = 9²- | BD |. | DC | If written, | BD |. | DC | = 32 cm².</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/yukseklik-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"yükseklik çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 2- (1): From the Pythagorean relation in ABC triangle | BC | = k.rok5. If we say | BD | = x; | DC | = kkök5-x. In triangle ABC k² = x.kk root5, x = k / root5 from the Euclidean relation. If k / root5 is written instead of x, since k = 2 root5, then | BC | = 10 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/oklid-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"öklid soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 2- (2): The height of the hypotenuse in a right triangle is found by dividing the product of perpendicular sides by the hypotenuse. This is called the area relation. It is covered with the subject of the Euclidean theorem. For the proof of this formula and to prove other formulas, see the geometry proof section.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 3: In a right triangle, the height of the hypotenuse squared is equal to the product of the lengths it separates from the corners. This is called the Euclidean theorem.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/45-45-90-ucgeni-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"45 45 90 üçgeni soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: If the right triangle is also isosceles, then the hypotenuse is equal to the root2 times the perpendicular sides.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dik-ucgen-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"dik üçgen çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Let’s straighten the extension BC from corner A. Write instead of angles and call edge 5 opposite 30 °. Since the hypotenuse is equal to the root2 of the right sides in an isosceles right triangle, we write 5root2 for the length AC.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ozel-ucgenler-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"özel üçgenler soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: There are many solutions to these questions. We can solve them practically by creating a 30 60 90 triangle or a 45 45 90 triangle.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ozel-ucgenler-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"özel üçgenler çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In 30 60 90 triangle, the side opposite 30 ° is half the length of the hypotenuse, and in an isosceles right triangle the hypotenuse is equal to the root of the right sides.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/30-60-90-ucgeni-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"30 60 90 üçgeni soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In a right triangle, if one of the right sides is equal to half the length of the hypotenuse, this triangle is 30 60 90 and the opposite corner is 30 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":152,\"width\":191,\"height\":191,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/pdf-indir.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-152\" width=\"191\" height=\"191\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"has-text-align-center\" id=\"special-right-triangles-test-1-pdf\">Special right triangles test-1 PDF</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Course Geometry offers Geometry textbook in pdf format that can be downloaded free of charge. Students can view the special right triangles test-1 pdf, which is important for university entrance exam, which aims to improve students\' problem solving skills.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button aligncenter\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'Special Right Triangles Test-1', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '164-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-02-18 14:31:16', '2022-02-18 11:31:16', '', 164, 'http://localhost/geometri/?p=165', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(163, 1, '2022-02-16 21:21:04', '2022-02-16 18:21:04', '<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-acilar-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende açılar soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 1-) If ABC is a triangle, m (DBA) = m (DCB), m (BDC) = 143 °; How many degrees is m (CBA) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende açı soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 2-) If ABC is a triangle, m (BAD) = m (DAC), m (CBA) – m (ACB) = 32 °; How many degrees is m (ADB)?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/fuze-kurali-sorulari-7.sinif_.jpg\" alt=\"füze kuralı soruları 7.sınıf\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 3-) If ABC is a triangle, [AD] perpendicular [BD], m (DBA) = m (DAC), m (CBA) = 40 °; How many degrees is m (ACB) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/iki-ic-aciortay-arasindaki-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"iki iç açıortay arasındaki açı soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 4-) If ABC is a triangle, [BD] and [CD] bisector, m (BAC) = 2x, m (BDC) = 6x; How many degrees is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-aciortaylarin-olusturdugu-acilar-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende açıortayların oluşturduğu açılar soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 5-) [BE parallel [CF, [AP] and [DP] bisector, if m (ABE) = 141 °, m (FCD) = 151 °; How many degrees is m (DPA) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ic-aciortay-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"iç açıortay açı soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 6-) If ABC is a triangle, [AE] and [BD] bisector, m (BDC) = 115 °, m (AEB) = 76 °; How many degrees is m (ACB) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/iki-dis-aciortay-arasindaki-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"iki dış açıortay arasındaki açı soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 7-) If ABC is a triangle, [BD] and [CD] bisector, m (EAF) = 14x, m (CDB) = 11x; How many degrees is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/dis-aciortay-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"dış açıortay açı soruları\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 8-) ABC is a triangle, [BD] and [CD] bisector, if m (EBF) = 44 °; How many degrees is m (ADC) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"angles-in-a-triangle-test-1-answers\">Angles in a triangle test-1 answers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-acilar-cozumlu-test.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende açılar çözümlü test\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 1: If the angle B is x, then the CBD angle is x-a. From the sum of the angles of the DBC triangle, x = 37 °</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 2: From the sum of the angles of the US triangle, x + n = 180 ° -m (ADB), in the ADC triangle from the outer angle y + n = m (ADB). Multiply the second expression by (-2) and add xy = 180 to the side by the first. ° -2m (ADB). If 32 ° is written instead of x, m (ADB) = 74 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-acilar-roket-kurali.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende açılar roket kuralı\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 3: The size of the angle formed when one side of the triangle is bent inward is x = a + b + c. The US concave quadrilateral contains x + a + 40 ° -a = 90 ° (shalwar, rocket, missile rule), x = 50 °. See geometry proofs section for proof of rule-Rocket rule-Missile rule and other proofs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 4: The size of the angle formed by the two inner bisectors in a triangle is 90 degrees more than half the size of the inside angle in the third corner, so 6x = 90 ° + x, x = 18 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ic-aciortay-ile-ilgili-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"iç açıortay ile ilgili çözümlü sorular\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 5: Let the extension [AB] and [DC] intersect at point K. With the rule of M, m (DKA) = 68 °. The dimension of the angle formed by the intersection of two bisector in the triangle AKD is x = 90 ° + (68 ° / 2) = 124 ° .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 6: Since [AE] and [BD] are bisectors in triangle ABC, m (AFB) = 90 ° + (x / 2). If the angles of the quadrant equal 360 °, then x = 34 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/iki-dis-aciortayin-kesisimi.jpg\" alt=\"iki dış açıortayın kesişimi\"/><figcaption>Angles in a triangle test-1 answers</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 7: The measure of the angle formed by the two outer bisectors in a triangle is the complement of half the measure of the angle in the third corner. 11x = 90 ° – (14x / 2), x = 5 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution 8: The angle between the two outer bisectors is x = 90 ° – (44 ° / 2) = 68 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":152,\"width\":187,\"height\":187,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/pdf-indir.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-152\" width=\"187\" height=\"187\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"has-text-align-center\" id=\"geometry-angles-in-a-triangle-test-1-pdf\">Geometry angles in a triangle test-1 PDF</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Course Geometry offers Geometry textbook in pdf format that can be downloaded free of charge. Students can view the angles in a triangle test-1 pdf, which is important for university entrance exam, which aims to improve students\' problem solving skills.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button aligncenter\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'Angles in a Triangle Test-1', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '154-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-02-16 21:21:04', '2022-02-16 18:21:04', '', 154, 'http://localhost/geometri/?p=163', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(168, 1, '2022-02-18 15:03:24', '2022-02-18 12:03:24', '<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/dik-ve-ozel-ucgenler-test-3.jpg\" alt=\"dik ve özel üçgenler test 3\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 1-) If ABC is an isosceles triangle, [BE] perpendicular [AC], | EC | = 3 cm, | BC | = 5 cm; | AC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen açı soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 2-) ABC is a triangle, [AK] perpendicular [BC], [PM] perpendicular [BC], | AB | = | PC |, | BK | = | KL |, | LM | = | MC |, m ( ACB) = 19 °; How many degrees is m (BAC)?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-uzunluk-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen uzunluk soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 3-) ABCD quadrilateral, [AP] perpendicular [BC], [AO] perpendicular [CD], m (PAO) = 45 ° | BP | = | PC |, | CO | = | OD |, C with point A If the distance between the point is 12 br; What is the distance between point B and point D?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-ornek-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen örnek sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 4-) If ABC is a right triangle, m (CBA) = 2m (DAC), | AB | = 15 cm, | AC | = 8 cm; | DC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 5-) If ABC is a triangle, m (ACB) = 2m (BAD), | AC | = | CD |, | AB | = 5 cm, | BD | = 1 cm; | AC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgende-aci-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgende açı soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 6-) ACD and BCE are each triangle, | BE | = | BC |, | AE | = | DC |, m (CBD) = m (DBE), m (ADC) = 120 °, m (CAD) = x if; How many degrees is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgende-dikme-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 7-) In triangle ABC [DE] perpendicular [AC], [DF] perpendicular [AB], if m (ACB) = m (CAB) = 15 °, | DE | + | DF | = 5 cm; | AB | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgende-diklik-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 8-) In triangle ABC [DF] perpendicular [AB], [DE] perpendicular [AC], | DF | = 1 cm, | DE | = 3 cm, | BC | = 2 root 5 cm; | AB | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"special-right-triangles-test-3-answers\">Special right triangles test-3 answers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/dik-ve-ozel-ucgenler-test-3-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"dik ve özel üçgenler test 3 çözümleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: EBC is the right triangle (3-4-5). If we say | AE | = x in ABC triangle, it is | AB | = x + 3. In right triangle ABE, x = 7/6 cm from Pythagoras relation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgende-aci-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgende açı soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: If we connect the point L with the point P in ABC triangle, isosceles triangles are formed. The angle A is found by writing the angles of the isosceles triangles.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgende-uzunluk-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgende uzunluk soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In two isosceles triangles that are formed, if we combine points A and C, the sum of the vertex angles of isosceles triangles is 2a + 2b, which is 90 degrees, since the heights are at the same time isosceles.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In the US triangle, the perpendicular descending from corner B becomes an isosceles triangle since the angles will be bisector when the angles are lettered. Since ABC is a right triangle, x = 2 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In an isosceles triangle, the height of the base is the bisector. If the angles are written, ABC is a right triangle and from the Pythagorean equation | AC | = 12 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In an isosceles triangle BCE, the bisector becomes both the height and the median at the same time. If we connect E with point D, in DCE triangle the triangle becomes isosceles since the median and the height are the same line. (There are two isosceles adjoined to the base, which is called the deltoid) In the AFD triangle, the angle x is 20 ° from the sum of internal angles.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgende-diklik-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgende diklik soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In an isosceles triangle, the sum of the perpendiculars drawn from a point taken on the base to the equilateral sides is equal to the height of the identical sides. If the side opposite 30 ° in a right triangle is 5 cm, then the hypotenuse will be 2 times the side opposite to 30 °, so the answer is 10 cm</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-diklik-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen diklik çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In an isosceles triangle, the sum of the posts lowered to equal sides from a forehead point on the base is equal to a height of equal sides. | BH | = 3 + 1 = 4 cm. If we say | AH | = x, then | AB | = x + 2. In the triangle ABH, from the Pythagorean equation, | AB | = | AC | = 5 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separato