(170, 1, '2022-02-18 15:04:03', '2022-02-18 12:04:03', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>30 60 90 triangle questions, 45 45 90 triangle questions, 15 75 90 triangle questions, center of perpendicularity questions, magnificent triple questions, special triangle questions, Pythagoras relation questions, 30 60 90 triangle solutions, orthogonal center questions, 15 75 Solving 90 triangle questions, Pythagoras solution questions</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dik-ve-ozel-ucgenler-test2.jpg\" alt=\"dik ve özel üçgenler test\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 1-) If ABC is a triangle, [BA] perpendicular [AC], | AD | = | BE | = | EC |, if m (CBA) = 30 °; How many degrees is m (DCE) = α?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/muhtesem-uclu-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"muhteşem üçlü soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 2-) ABC is a triangle, if [PA] perpendicular [AC], m (BAP) = 15 °, m (ACP) = 25 °; | PC | / | AB | What is the rate?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ozel-ucgen-soru.jpg\" alt=\"özel üçgen soru\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 3-) ABC is a triangle, [BK] perpendicular [AC], | BL | = | LC |, | BK | = | AL | if; How many degrees is m (LAC) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/diklik-merkezi-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"diklik merkezi soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 4-) If point E on [BD] is the cut off point of the heights of triangle ABC, | BE | = 4k root3 cm, | ED | = root3 cm, m (ACB) = 60 °; | AC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/15-75-90-ucgeni-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"15 75 90 üçgeni soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 5-) If ABC right triangle, [BA] perpendicular [AC], [AE] perpendicular [BC], | BD | = | DC |, | AD | = 10 cm, m (ACB) = 15 °; | AE | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/45-45-90-ucgeni-ile-ilgili-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"45 45 90 üçgeni ile ilgili sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 6-) If ABC is a triangle, [DA] perpendicular [AC], m (BAD) = 45 °, | AD | = root2 cm, | AC | = 2 root2 cm; | AB | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/pisagor-bagintisi-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"pisagor bağıntısı soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 7-) If points A, D and E are linear, [AE] perpendicular [BC], | AD | = 7 cm, | AC | = 8 cm, | BD | = 3 cm in triangle ABC; | DC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/kenarlarina-gore-ozel-ucgen-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"kenarlarına göre özel üçgen soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 8-) ABC and CBD are a triangle each, [AB] perpendicular [BD], | CB | = | CD |, | AC | = | BD | if; How many degrees is m (BAC) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"special-right-triangles-test-2-answers\">Special right triangles test-2 answers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dik-ve-ozel-ucgenler-test2-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"dik ve özel üçgenler test2 çözümleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: If we call the hypotenuse length 2 br in ABC triangle (30 60 90), the side opposite 30 ° is 1 br. The ABC triangle becomes isosceles (45 45 90), since α + 45 ° = 60 °, α = 15 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/muhtesem-uclu-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"muhteşem üçlü soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: The measure of angle B from the sum of the angles of triangle ABC is 50 °. If we draw a median of the hypotenuse in the right triangle APC, the median length of the hypotenuse is equal to half the hypotenuse (perfect triple-super triple). Accordingly, m (ASB) = 50 ° in the ABS triangle. AB | = | AS | then | PC | / | AB | rate is 2.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/30-60-90-ucgeni-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"30 60 90 üçgeni çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Since the base of triangle ABC is divided into two equal parts, the ratio of parallel similar triangles we will draw makes 2, so that the hypotenuse in the right triangle ALM is 2 times the vertical side. The angle x angle of the corner opposite this right side will be 30 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/diklik-merkezi-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"diklik merkezi soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: If point E is the center of perpendicularity in triangle ABC, [BD] is perpendicular to [AC]. If we draw a line from corner A so that it passes through point E, it will cross [BC] perpendicularly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/15-75-90-ucgeni-soru-cozumu.jpg\" alt=\"15 75 90 üçgeni soru çözümü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Since ABC is the median of right triangle [BD], | BC | = 20 cm. Since ABC is a 15 75 90 triangle, the height of the hypotenuse is one quarter of the hypotenuse, so the height = x = 5 cm. (Proven)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dik-ucgen-sorulari-cozumlu.jpg\" alt=\"dik üçgen soruları çözümlü\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Let’s draw parallel to AB from point D in triangle ABC. Since the triangle of AED will be an isosceles right triangle, AD is root2 and the length of DE from similar triangles formed is the middle of the USA triangle. Since the length of AED is 2 cm, AB length is 4 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/pisagor-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"pisagor çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: If we take the symmetry of the BDC triangle in the ABC triangle, an ABFC quadrilateral whose diagonals intersect perpendicularly is 7² + x² = 8² + 3². From here, x = 2 root6 is found. (Proven)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/30-60-90-ucgeni-cozumlu-ornek.jpg\" alt=\"30 60 90 üçgeni çözümlü örnek\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In an isosceles triangle, the height of the base is also the median. If we say | BE | = | ED | = a cm, from the FBEC rectangle, | BE | = | FC | = a cm. The hypotenuse in the AFC right triangle | FC | Since it is twice of, the measure of the angle x is 30°.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":152,\"width\":164,\"height\":164,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/pdf-indir.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-152\" width=\"164\" height=\"164\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"has-text-align-center\" id=\"special-right-triangles-test-2-pdf\">Special right triangles test-2 PDF</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Course Geometry offers Geometry textbook in pdf format that can be downloaded free of charge. Students can view the special right triangles test-2 pdf, which is important for university entrance exam, which aims to improve students\' problem solving skills</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button aligncenter\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons -->', 'Special Right Triangles Test-2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '166-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-02-18 15:04:03', '2022-02-18 12:04:03', '', 166, 'http://localhost/geometri/?p=170', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(171, 1, '2022-02-18 15:09:39', '2022-02-18 12:09:39', '<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/dik-ve-ozel-ucgenler-test-4.jpg\" alt=\"dik ve özel üçgenler test 4\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 1-) ABC is a triangle, [CK] perpendicular [AB], [EP] perpendicular [AB], [ED] perpendicular [AD], | AB | = | AC |, | PE | + | KC | = 2 | If BC |, | KB | = root17 cm, | ED | = 2 cm; | BC | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":172,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/image.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-172\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 2-) In triangle ABC | AB | = | AC |, [FD] parallel [AC], [DE] perpendicular [AC], | AE | = 6 cm, | EC | = 2 cm, | FB | = 3 cm if; | DE | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgende-yukseklik-sorulari.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgende yükseklik soruları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 3-) If ABC and DBE are right triangles, | DC | = | CE |, | AD | = 5 cm, | DB | = 8 cm; | DE | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-sorulari-kolay.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soruları kolay\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 4-) ABC isosceles triangle, | AB | = | BC |, [BD] perpendicular [AC], [BD] and the cut-off point of [CE] F, | BF | = | FD |, | BE | = 1 cm , | BC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-problemleri.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen problemleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 5-) ABE and DBC are each triangle, [AE] parallel [BC], [DC] perpendicular [BC], m (CBD) = m (EBA), | AE | = | BD |, | AB | = 13 cm If | DC | = 5 cm; | DE | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-sorulari-ve-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soruları ve çözümleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 6-) If ABC is triangle in the figure, [AB] perpendicular [AC], [DE] perpendicular [BC], [FD] bisector, | BE | = | EC |, if m (FDE) = 74 °; How many degrees is m (FCB) = α?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-ile-ilgili-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 7-) If ABC triangle, [AD] perpendicular [BD], | BC | = 2 | AD |, m (BAD) = m (DAC) = 53 °; How many degrees is m (DBC) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-ile-ilgili-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen ile ilgili sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 8-) ABC right triangle, if | BE | = 2 | CD |, m (CBA) = 20 °, m (CDA) = 40 °; How many degrees is m (DAE) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"special-right-triangles-test-4-answers\">Special right triangles test-4 answers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/dik-ve-ozel-ucgenler-test-4-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"dik ve özel üçgenler test 4 çözümleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: If we say | BC | = x, we have | PE | + | KC | = 2x. In the isosceles triangle ABC | PE | = | KC | + | ED |</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>| KC | +2+ | KC | = 2x, from here | KC | = x-1. If the Pythagorean relation is written in the KBC triangle, | BC | = x = 9 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-sorulari-ve-cozumleri-9-sinif.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soruları ve çözümleri 9 sınıf\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In the isosceles triangle ABC, [FD] is parallel to [AC], and [DF] is perpendicular to the corresponding angles | FD | = 3 cm and [ED], since FDER is rectangular | FR | = x cm, | RE | = 3 cm, | AF | = 8-3 = 5 cm, | AR | = 6-3 = 3 cm, in AFR right triangle there is x = 4 cm from the pythagoras.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-soru-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soru çözümleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In the DBC right triangle | DC | = | CE | is | DC | = | BC | = | CE | (the magnificent triad). | BC | = | CE | And since it is perpendicular to [AC] and [BE], if we connect points A with E, the triangle ABE becomes isosceles. | AC | = 13 cm. Since the triangle of AD will have a 5-12-13 right triangle, | DE | = 12 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-soru-cevap.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soru cevap\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In DBC triangle | DK | = | BK | is | DK | = | BK | = | KC | (magnificent triple). Since | DL | = 1 cm from the same triangles, | DK | = (x / 2) -1. From the similarity of the two triangles, x = 3 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-sorulari-ve-cevaplari.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soruları ve cevapları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Since the angles between the two sides of the isosceles triangle DBK and the triangle ABE are equal, these triangles are equal. Since DBC will be 5-12-13 right triangle, | BC | = 12 cm. | BK | = | BE | = 24 cm. From here | DE | = x = 24-13 = 11 cm is calculated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-ile-ilgili-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen ile ilgili çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Let’s connect the point K where the extension of [BA] and [ED] intersects to point C. KBC is an isosceles triangle since the height is also median. If a triangle has two inner bisectors, the third is the bisector. According to this, in KFC triangle [CA] is bisector. Since [CA] is bisector and height, KFC triangle is isosceles. If we call the base angles 2β, it is = 37 ° from the external angle. Since m (CLD) = 37 ° + 74 ° = α + 90 °, m (FCB) = α = 21 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-soru-cozumlu-test.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soru çözümlü test\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: The point K where [AC] and the extension of [BD] intersect makes the triangle ABK isosceles. If we draw parallel to [AK] from point D, | BD | = | DK | Since the triangles have a similarity ratio of 2, | BC | = 2 | DE | dir. | BC | = 2 | AD | was. Accordingly | AD | = | DE | Since it will be, m (AED) = 53 ° and m (KDE) = x from corresponding angles. x + 37 ° = 53 °, x = 16 ° are calculated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgende-aci-soru-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgende açı soru çözümleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Outside angle m (BAD) = 20 °. Since m (CBA) = m (BAD) = 20 ° | BD | = | AD | Dir. | EC | = a, | DE | = b, then | BD | = 2a + b. | BD | = | AD | = 2a + b. Let’s take a point P such that the triangle ADP is isosceles. m (APD) = 40 °, | CP | = a + b. Since | AP | = | EP | = 2a + b, in AEP triangle m (PEA) = m (EAP) = 70 °. x + 40 ° = 70 °, x = 30 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":152,\"width\":147,\"height\":147,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/pdf-indir.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-152\" width=\"147\" height=\"147\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"has-text-align-center\" id=\"special-right-triangles-test-4-pdf\">Special right triangles test-4 PDF</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Course Geometry offers Geometry textbook in pdf format that can be downloaded free of charge. Students can view the special right triangles test-4 pdf, which is important for university entrance exam, which aims to improve students\' problem solving skills.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button {\"align\":\"center