ri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-problemleri.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen problemleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 5-) ABE and DBC are each triangle, [AE] parallel [BC], [DC] perpendicular [BC], m (CBD) = m (EBA), | AE | = | BD |, | AB | = 13 cm If | DC | = 5 cm; | DE | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-sorulari-ve-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soruları ve çözümleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 6-) If ABC is triangle in the figure, [AB] perpendicular [AC], [DE] perpendicular [BC], [FD] bisector, | BE | = | EC |, if m (FDE) = 74 °; How many degrees is m (FCB) = α?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-ile-ilgili-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 7-) If ABC triangle, [AD] perpendicular [BD], | BC | = 2 | AD |, m (BAD) = m (DAC) = 53 °; How many degrees is m (DBC) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-ile-ilgili-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen ile ilgili sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 8-) ABC right triangle, if | BE | = 2 | CD |, m (CBA) = 20 °, m (CDA) = 40 °; How many degrees is m (DAE) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"special-right-triangles-test-4-answers\">Special right triangles test-4 answers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/dik-ve-ozel-ucgenler-test-4-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"dik ve özel üçgenler test 4 çözümleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: If we say | BC | = x, we have | PE | + | KC | = 2x. In the isosceles triangle ABC | PE | = | KC | + | ED |</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>| KC | +2+ | KC | = 2x, from here | KC | = x-1. If the Pythagorean relation is written in the KBC triangle, | BC | = x = 9 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-sorulari-ve-cozumleri-9-sinif.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soruları ve çözümleri 9 sınıf\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In the isosceles triangle ABC, [FD] is parallel to [AC], and [DF] is perpendicular to the corresponding angles | FD | = 3 cm and [ED], since FDER is rectangular | FR | = x cm, | RE | = 3 cm, | AF | = 8-3 = 5 cm, | AR | = 6-3 = 3 cm, in AFR right triangle there is x = 4 cm from the pythagoras.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-soru-cozumleri.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soru çözümleri\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In the DBC right triangle | DC | = | CE | is | DC | = | BC | = | CE | (the magnificent triad). | BC | = | CE | And since it is perpendicular to [AC] and [BE], if we connect points A with E, the triangle ABE becomes isosceles. | AC | = 13 cm. Since the triangle of AD will have a 5-12-13 right triangle, | DE | = 12 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-soru-cevap.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soru cevap\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: In DBC triangle | DK | = | BK | is | DK | = | BK | = | KC | (magnificent triple). Since | DL | = 1 cm from the same triangles, | DK | = (x / 2) -1. From the similarity of the two triangles, x = 3 cm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-sorulari-ve-cevaplari.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soruları ve cevapları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Since the angles between the two sides of the isosceles triangle DBK and the triangle ABE are equal, these triangles are equal. Since DBC will be 5-12-13 right triangle, | BC | = 12 cm. | BK | = | BE | = 24 cm. From here | DE | = x = 24-13 = 11 cm is calculated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-ile-ilgili-cozumlu-sorular.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen ile ilgili çözümlü sorular\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: Let’s connect the point K where the extension of [BA] and [ED] intersects to point C. KBC is an isosceles triangle since the height is also median. If a triangle has two inner bisectors, the third is the bisector. According to this, in KFC triangle [CA] is bisector. Since [CA] is bisector and height, KFC triangle is isosceles. If we call the base angles 2β, it is = 37 ° from the external angle. Since m (CLD) = 37 ° + 74 ° = α + 90 °, m (FCB) = α = 21 °.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/ikizkenar-ucgen-soru-cozumlu-test.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen soru çözümlü test\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution: The point K where [AC] and the extension of [BD] intersect makes the triangle ABK isosceles. If we draw parallel to [AK] from point D, | BD | = | DK | Since the triangles have a similarity ratio of 2, | BC | = 2 | DE | di