(196, 1, '2022-02-21 12:29:19', '2022-02-21 09:29:19', '<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"left\",\"id\":197,\"width\":369,\"height\":207,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/geometri-ders-notlari-600x336-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-197\" width=\"369\" height=\"207\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the <strong>Geometry</strong> Private Lesson <strong>Notes</strong>, which contain questions and answers, you can get information that allows you to look at the classical or new generation questions that are likely to come up with a clear and simple explanation, from a broad perspective, and to interpret them correctly, without causing confusion.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even if you’re a student in a classroom, if you don’t take math-geometry grades properly and always write them on the back of the paper, you don’t have the concept of “review” or “review”, so you won’t have grades.If you don’t understand something in a topic or problem, be it a Mathematics-Geometry course or any other course, you tend to get bored with writing notes.If you quit, you won’t even think about going back and reviewing it later.Even if you don’t understand a problem during class, when you get home, you can look at your notebook and say, “It’s really simple!” you might think! Please do your best not to leave your <a href=\"https://dersgeometri.com/en/geometry/\"><strong>geometry</strong></a> notebook empty.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator {\"color\":\"cyan-bluish-gray\",\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-text-color has-background has-cyan-bluish-gray-background-color has-cyan-bluish-gray-color is-style-default\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ikizkenar-ucgen-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In ABC isosceles triangle (| AB | = | AC |), [DE] perpendicular [AB], [DF] perpendicular [AC], m (BAC) = 30 °, | ED | = 3 cm, | DF | = 4 cm if; | AB | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ikizkenar-ucgen-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"ikizkenar üçgen notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In an isosceles triangle, the sum of the posts lowered to equal sides from a point taken on the base is equal to a height belonging to the equal sides. (An isosceles triangle proof)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/eskenar-ucgen-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"eşkenar üçgen ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC equilateral triangle, if m (AFB) = 150 °, | FB | = 8 cm, | FC | = 17 cm; | AF | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/aci-kenar-bagintilari-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"açı kenar bağıntıları ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC and DEC are triangles with integer sides, [AB] perpendicular [AC], | AD | = | DC |, | AB | = 5 cm, | EC | = 7 cm; How many cm is the largest integer value of | DE | = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/aciortay-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"açıortay ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is a triangle, if m (BAD) = m (DAC) = 60 °, | AB | = 6 cm, | AD | = 4 cm; | DC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-kenarortay-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende kenarortay ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is a triangle, center of gravity G, [BA] perpendicular [AC], [GE] perpendicular [BC], if m (ACB) = 15 °, | GE | = 2 cm; | BC | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/benzerlik-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"benzerlik ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is an isosceles triangle shaped cardboard, [AH] perpendicular [BC], | AB | = | AC |, | AH | = 25 cm. When folded along [DE], corner A coincides with corner C. [DE] ∩ [AH Since] = {K}; | AK | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-benzerlik-ders-notu.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende benzerlik ders notu\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC triangle, [AB] perpendicular [CD], [AC] perpendicular [BE], | BE | = 3 | EC |, | DC | = 2 | DB | if; How many degrees is m (BAC)?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/benzerlik-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"benzerlik notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Üçgen sorusunun diğer bir çözümü (Trigonometri ile çözüm)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/eslik-ve-benzerlik-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"eşlik ve benzerlik notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is a right triangle, KLMN is a square, [AB] perpendicular [AC], | AC | = 2 | AB |, | BN | = 10 cm; | BC | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/eslik-ve-benzerlik-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"eşlik ve benzerlik ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is a triangle, [AD] perpendicular [DC], if m (BAD) = 30 °, | AB | = 4 cm, | CD | = 6 cm; | BE | / | EC | What is the rate?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/9.sinif-eslik-ve-benzerlik-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"9.sınıf eşlik ve benzerlik ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is a triangle, [AF] and [BF] bisector, [DE] parallel [AB], | AD | = 4 cm, | BE | = 5 cm, | AB | = 12 cm; How many cm is the circumference (DEC)?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-benzerlik-9.sinif_.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende benzerlik 9.sınıf\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If ABC is a triangle, [DF] parallel [AC], [EF] parallel [DC], | BE | = 4 cm, | AD | = 3 cm; | ED | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgenlerde-eslik-ve-benzerlik-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgenlerde eşlik ve benzerlik ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If ABC right triangle, [BD] and [CE] bisector, [AB] right [AC], | AD | = 2 cm, | DC | = 3 cm; | EC | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/tyt-ucgende-alan-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"tyt üçgende alan ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is a right triangle, [AB] perpendicular [AC], [BD] ∩ [EC] = {G}, | BE | = 4 cm, | CD | = 5 cm, If Area (AEGD) = Area (GBC); What is the area of ​​the triangle AED in cm²?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/9.-sinif-ucgende-alan-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"9. sınıf üçgende alan ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is a right triangle, if [AB] perpendicular [AE], [AC] perpendicular [BC], [BD] ∩ [EC] = {G}, | BD | = 6 cm, | DE | = 4 cm; How many cm² is the area (ABE)?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-alan-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende alan ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC equilateral triangle, if m (CED) = 120 °, | ED | = | EC |, | DC | = 2 | BD |, | AB | = 6 root3 cm; What is the area of ​​the triangle AEC in cm²?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgende-alan-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgende alan notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In ABC triangle, if E perpendicular center, A, D, E, F is linear, [BD] perpendicular [DC], Area (BEC) = 8 cm², Area (ABC) = 18 cm²; How many cm² is the area (BDCE)?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgenler-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgenler ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is a triangle, [DE] perpendicular [AB], [AC] perpendicular [BC], if m (CFA) = 80 °, m (CBA) = 40 °; How many degrees is m (DAC) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgenler-ders-notu.jpg\" alt=\"üçgenler ders notu\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solution using quadrilateral of beams.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/matematik-ucgenler-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"matematik üçgenler ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is a triangle, [CE] perpendicular [AB], [BD] perpendicular [AC], if m (CFD) = 20 °, m (ACB) = 50 °; How many degrees is m (BAC) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/geometri-ucgenler-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"geometri üçgenler ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is a triangle, if | DA | = | DC |, m (BAE) = 10 °, m (DCB) = 20 °, m (DEB) = 80 °; How many degrees is m (AED) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ucgen-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"üçgen ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABC is a triangle, if | BD | = root2 cm, | DC | = 1 cm, m (ACB) = 22.5 °, m (CBA) = 15 °; How many degrees is m (DAC) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/10.sinif-matematik-dikdortgen-ders-notlari.jpg\" alt=\"10.sınıf matematik dikdörtgen ders notları\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ABCD rectangle, if m (AEF) = m (DEF), m (AEB) = m (BEC), | EF | = 6 cm, | EB | = 8 cm; | AF | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-