(205, 1, '2022-02-21 12:49:22', '2022-02-21 09:49:22', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Angle in Triangle, Angle in Rectangle, Area in Trapezoid, Geometry Trapezoid Area, Inner Tangent Circle Center, Outer Tangent Circle Center, Area in Square, Angle Edge Relations, Octagon, Area in Quadrilateral, Euclidean, 30 60 90 Triangle, Isosceles Angle, Area of ​​a Triangle, Equilateral Triangle Angle, Right Triangle Length, Isosceles Triangle Length, Angles in Quadrilaterals, Hexagonal Area, Isosceles Triangle, Equilateral Triangle, 30 60 90 Triangles, Circumferential Angle, Isosceles Trapezoid, Right Trapezoid, Right Trapezoid Area, Tangent Beam Circumference Angle, Circular de Angle, Area in a Circle, Trigonometry Triangle, Deltoid, Length in a Circle, Area on a Paralleloal Edge, Pythagorean Relation, Magnificent Triangle, Transport Questions in a Triangle</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-01.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 1-) In the figure, A, B, C points are linear, m (EBA); All 1/3 of m (CBD) if m (CBD) = m (DBE) + 10 °; How many degrees is m (DBE)?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-02.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 2-) If [FG parallel [BA, [FE] parallel [CD], m (DCB)) = 130 °, m (ABC) = 4x-10 °, m (EFG) = 3x; How many degrees is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-03.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 3-) If FK parallel [CR, [CP parallel [DA], [AE] and [CE] bisector, 3m (RCE) = 2m (DAE); How many degrees is m (EBA) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-04.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 4-) [BA parallel [EF parallel HG, if m (ABC) = m (EDC), m (DEF) = 100 °; How many degrees is m (DCB) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-05.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 5-) [BE parallel if [CF, m (ABE) = 150 °, m (BAD) = 60 °, m (ADC) = 50 °; How many degrees is m (FCD) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-06.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 6-) [AF parallel [DE, [AC] perpendicular [BD], [AC] bisector, if m (BDE) = 145 °; How many degrees is m (DBA) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-07.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 7-) If FE parallel [CD, m (GAE) = 5y-5 °, m (DCB) = 3y + 5 °, m (GBC) = 60 °; How many degrees is m (FAB) = x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- w