(232, 1, '2022-02-21 13:20:34', '2022-02-21 10:20:34', '<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0131.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 131-) In the figure, ABCD is rectangular, parallel to [BE] [CF], if 2 | AE | = 3 | EF |, | BE | = 3 root2 cm, | CF | = 13 root2 cm, m (BCF) = 45 °; What is the area of ​​the rectangle?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0132.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 132-) ABCD square, S; If the cut-off point of [AC] and [EF] is | BF | = 3 cm, | ED | = 6 cm, | AB | = 18 cm; How many cm² is the area of ​​the SFC triangle?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0133.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 133-) If the area of ​​ABCD square, | DF | = | FC |, FKLN convex quadrilateral is 18 cm²; What is the length of a square in centimeters?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0134.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 134-) ABCD square, perpendicular to [AP] [PN], perpendicular to [PN] [NC], | AP | = | PN | = | NC | if; What is the area of ​​the square in cm²?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0135.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 135-) If ABCD is rectangle, [AC] diagonal, perpendicular to [SN] [ND], | AB | = | NC |, | AS | = 1 cm, | SD | = 8 cm; | AN | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0136.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 136-) If PEFT and TKMN are square, perpendicular to [TR] [FK], PRNT concave quadrilateral is 144 cm²; | TR | how many cm?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0137.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 137-) ABCD is trapezoid, [AB] parallel [DC], if the measure of angle D is twice the measure of angle B, the length of the bottom base is 13 cm, the length of [AD] is 8 cm; What is the length of the upper sole?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0138.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 138-) ABCD steep trapezoid, | AB | ² + | BC | ² = 8 | BC | if the length of the upper base is 4 cm; how many cm is the side x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0139.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 139-) ABCD is trapezoid, [ED] perpendicular [DC], point E is the midpoint of the subbase, 2 | DA | = 3 | EB |, if the height is 2 root 5 cm; What is the total of shaded areas in cm²?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0140.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 140-) If the diagonals of the trapezoid ABCD are perpendicular to each other, the length of the upper base is 3 cm, the length of the lower base is 8 cm; how many cm is the side x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0141.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 141-) ABCD isosceles trapezoid, CAB right triangle, lower base 3 times the upper base, | AD | = 6 cm, | CE | = | EB | if; | AE | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0142.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 142-) If ABCD is trapezoid perpendicular, [DE] and [CE] bisector, | BC | = 9 cm, | AB | = 12 cm; What is the area of ​​the ECD triangle?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://www.dersgeometri.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/geometri-sorulari-0143.jpg\" alt=\"geometri soruları\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Question 143-) ABCD is trapezoid perpendicular, diagonals 6 cm-8 cm and perpendicular to each other, m (EAC) = m (AEC), if the lower floor is 4 times the upper floor; | BE | = how many cm is x?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Geometry Test-10', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'geometry-test-10', '', '', '2022-02-21 13:20:36', '2022-02-21 10:20:36', '', 0, 'http://localhost/geometri/?p=232', 0, 'post', '', 0),
