INSERT INTO `gtm_term_taxonomy` (`term_taxonomy_id`, `term_id`, `taxonomy`, `description`, `parent`, `count`) VALUES
(1, 1, 'category', '', 0, 5),
(2, 2, 'wp_theme', '', 0, 1),
(4, 4, 'category', '<div class=\"cat-edit\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"cat-img alignnone wp-image-35 size-medium\" src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/geometri-ders-konulari-1-600x336-1-450x252.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"252\" />\r\n<div class=\"cat-content\">YKS (Higher Education Institutions Exam) 1st session TYT (Basic Proficiency Test) and 2nd session AYT (Field Proficiency Test)’s 40-question Mathematics test, which topics can be derived from <strong>Geometry </strong><strong>questions</strong> (Geometry curriculum topics) and in previous years You can find out the distribution of the questions on the topics from the tables shown below.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<ul class=\"sub-cat-list\">\r\n 	<li>1)  Angles in a Line and Triangle</li>\r\n 	<li>2)  Perpendicular and Special Triangles</li>\r\n 	<li>3)  Equilateral Triangle and Equilateral Triangle</li>\r\n 	<li>4)  Area in a Triangle</li>\r\n 	<li>5)  Bilateral Relations in Triangle</li>\r\n 	<li>6)  Mediameter Relations in a Triangle</li>\r\n 	<li>7)  Society and Similarity in Triangle</li>\r\n 	<li>8)  Angle-Side Relationships</li>\r\n 	<li>9)  Polygons</li>\r\n 	<li>10)  Rectangles</li>\r\n 	<li>11)  Trapezoid</li>\r\n 	<li>12)  Parallelogram</li>\r\n 	<li>13)  Rhombus – Deltoid</li>\r\n 	<li>14)  Rectangle-Square</li>\r\n 	<li>15)  Circle and Circle</li>\r\n 	<li>16)  Area in the Apartment</li>\r\n 	<li>17)  Orthogonal Coordinate System</li>\r\n 	<li>18)  Analytics of the Point</li>\r\n 	<li>19)  Analytics of Truth</li>\r\n 	<li>20)  Conversions</li>\r\n 	<li>21)  Analytics of the Circle</li>\r\n 	<li>22)  Solid Bodies (Prism, Pyramid, Cone, Sphere)</li>\r\n</ul>', 0, 0),
(13, 13, 'category', 'Most Geometry tests require you to know a lot about triangles, in which students will use all properties, including height, median, bisector, perpendicular center, center of gravity, circumference, and area to solve the missing parts of triangles and polygons made up of triangles.Remember the rules and answer the geometry questions.The triangle tests collected under 7 subheadings are as follows;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Angles on a straight line</li>\r\n 	<li>Angles in a triangle</li>\r\n 	<li>Special right triangles</li>\r\n 	<li>Üçgende Alan</li>\r\n 	<li>Üçgende Açıortay Bağıntıları</li>\r\n 	<li>Üçgende Kenarortay Bağıntıları</li>\r\n 	<li>Açı-Kenar Bağıntıları</li>\r\n</ul>', 12, 9),
(14, 14, 'category', 'There are Geometry tests that allow you to practice and answer problems using the basic properties of various quadrilaterals such as general quadrilaterals, parallelogram, rhombus, rectangle, square, deltoid, trapezoid.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Dörtgenler</li>\r\n 	<li>Yamuk</li>\r\n 	<li>Paralelkenar</li>\r\n 	<li>Eşkenar Dörtgen</li>\r\n 	<li>Dikdörtgen-Kare</li>\r\n 	<li>Deltoid</li>\r\n</ul>', 12, 0),
(15, 15, 'nav_menu', '', 0, 8),
(18, 18, 'category', 'There are basic level questions related to the Geometry lesson.These problems are; It is about finding areas and circles of triangles, quadrilaterals, parallelograms, rectangles, and other shapes.Various problems with finding angles are also included.\r\n\r\nThe questions are mostly based on simple Geometry concepts or theorems that we all go through in our high school textbooks, but there are some tough ones, and the problem needs to be understood before trying to find a solution.\r\n\r\nYou can test your skills on a range of geometry tests. Detailed solutions are provided in the <a title=\"Geometry Textbook PDF\" href=\"https://dersimizgeometri.com/geometry-textbook-pdf/\"><em><strong>Geometry PDF</strong></em></a> page.', 12, 11),
(12, 12, 'category', '<div class=\"cat-edit\"><img class=\"cat-img alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost/geometri/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/matematik-test-coz-600x336-1-450x252.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<div class=\"\"><strong>Math Test Solutions</strong> As we all know, the effect of mathematics lesson on university placement; It has a 50 percent effect on the calculation of numerical and equally weighted score types in the university first exam and 20 percent on the calculation of the verbal score type.However, the effect of the first exam score we will receive on the university score to be calculated will be 40 percent.Therefore, Mathematics-Geometry is the lesson that needs to be solved the most tests.Classical questions were prioritized in order to understand Mathematics-Geometry issues and to have sufficient experience in solving the questions that will arise in the exam.</div>\r\n</div>', 0, 0);
